# =============================================================================
# рҹҡЁ PROJECT-SPECIFIC RULES (HIGHEST PRIORITY)
# =============================================================================

## Project Overview
Unified export and management tool for AI chat records (ChatGPT, Gemini, Claude).
- **Tech Stack**: Vue 3 + TypeScript + Vite + IndexedDB + Chrome Extension
- **Architecture**: npm workspaces monorepo

## Project-Specific Commit Scopes
| Scope | Description |
|---|---|
| `shared` | Shared utilities and types |
| `parser` | Chat export parsers |
| `extension` | Browser extension |
| `web-app` | Web application |
| `docs` | Documentation |

**Examples**:
- `feat(parser): add Gemini export parser`
- `fix(extension): resolve content script injection issue`
- `refactor(shared): optimize type definitions`

## Project Structure
```
AIchat-export-platform/
в”ңв”Җв”Җ packages/
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ shared/            # Shared types (Scope: shared)
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ parser/            # Chat parsers (Scope: parser)
в”Ӯ   в”ңв”Җв”Җ extension/         # Browser extension (Scope: extension)
в”Ӯ   в””в”Җв”Җ web-app/           # Web UI (Scope: web-app)
в””в”Җв”Җ docs/
    в””в”Җв”Җ ARCHITECTURE.md    # System architecture
```

## Documentation Triggers
When these keywords appear, check if `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` needs update:
- `parser`, `и§ЈжһҗеҷЁ` вҶ’ Module list, parsing flow
- `view`, `й Ғйқў`, `component` вҶ’ Web App page flow
- `type`, `interface`, `еһӢеҲҘ` вҶ’ Data model section
- `IndexedDB`, `storage` вҶ’ Storage architecture
- `extension`, `ж“ҙе……еҠҹиғҪ` вҶ’ Extension architecture
- `API`, `endpoint` вҶ’ Platform API reference

## Development Commands
```bash
npm run dev:web          # Web App dev server
npm run dev:extension    # Browser Extension dev
npm run build:all        # Build all packages (MUST run before commit)
npm run lint             # ESLint check
```

## Before Committing (Project-Specific)
- [ ] Run `npm run build:all` вҶ’ Ensure TypeScript compiles
- [ ] Run `npm run lint` вҶ’ Check code style
- [ ] Check if `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` needs update

# =============================================================================
# рҹ”Ҫ GLOBAL SHARED RULES (INHERITED)
# =============================================================================

## Git Workflow
- **Commit**: Per milestone, Conventional Commits: `<type>(<scope>): <subject>`
- **Branch Naming**: `<type>/<name>-<version>`
  - `feature/`: Own sequence (`sec`, `third`, ...)
  - `fix/`: Independent sequence (`first`, `sec`, ...)
- **Flow**: `Implement вҶ’ Auto Commit вҶ’ Auto Push вҶ’ Auto PR вҶ’ [Manual Merge]`
- **PR**: Title and Description MUST be in **з№Ғй«”дёӯж–Ү**
- вҡ пёҸ **NEVER** auto-merge or push directly to `main`

## Mandatory Test Flow Report
```markdown
### рҹ§Ә Test Flow Report
1. **Setup**: [Commands to prepare environment]
2. **Execution**: [CLI/API/Browser actions]
3. **Expected**: [What should happen?]
4. **Verification**: [Browser dev tools, console check]
```

## Safety & Quality
- **Data Safety**: NEVER edit binary/auto-generated files manually
- **Secrets**: NEVER commit `.env` files
- **Architecture Docs**: Auto-update `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` on structure changes
- **Language**: Always respond in **з№Ғй«”дёӯж–Ү**
- **Build Check**: `npm run build:all` must pass before commit

## Bug Fix Workflow
1. Check current branch for uncommitted changes (commit/stash first if needed)
2. Create fix branch: `git checkout main && git checkout -b fix/<name>-<version>`
3. Fix вҶ’ commit вҶ’ push вҶ’ PR
4. After merge: `git checkout <original-branch> && git rebase main`
5. Continue original development

## Session Recovery
When resuming development:
```bash
git branch --show-current
git status
git log --oneline -5
git stash list
```

## WIP Commits (Optional)
```
feat(component): WIP - feature 50% complete

[WIP] indicates in-progress
Next: complete XYZ integration
```

